Whisk the dressing ingredients together in a bowl and set aside.To make the salad, heat a tablespoon of the oil in a pan and add the garlic, carrot, red pepper and half the shallot. Cook for 5 minutes, or until softened. Stir in the lentils and half of the dressing.To make the tofu, put the flour and cashew milk into a bowl and whisk to a batter. Put the breadcrumbs in a shallow bowl.Rub a spoonful of the tofu with the miso paste and drop it into the batter. Transfer to the breadcrumbs and gently roll until completely covered. Repeat with the remaining tofu.Heat the oil in a frying pan and fry the tofu for 5â€“10 minutes, or until golden brown.Dress the kale and frisee in the remaining dressing. Add the remaining shallot and the herbs.Layer the salad with the lentils and jerky and finish with the fried tofu.